                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.626/317: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wallace</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract—Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-03-11T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 11, 1921—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>144. B–215 for Boyden.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <p>3. Pending decision of Department as to its attitude toward the Reparation
                    Commission, you are requested to maintain your staff and organization intact so
                    far as possible. You should give no publicity to the fact that you are retaining
                    staff. Present action does not indicate in any way whatever the possible
                    attitude of Department toward the Commission or the reparation settlement.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
